property_address: Entire guest house in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Welcome to our newly remodeled 1-bedroom abode! A quick 20-minute drive from the hustle and bustle of downtown Flagstaff, enjoy complete serenity, cozied within the pines. Our house is located on 3 acres right at the base of the Snowbowl ski resort, making it the ideal location for winter ski trips. Just a little over an hour from the Grand Canyon (only 3 stop signs!), adventure awaits year-round. Enjoy the wildlife (elk, many birds, etc), incredible stargazing, trails, and more.The spaceLocated off the beaten path, this historic house was home to Lou Bader, a local figure of whom the neighborhood was named after, until his passing in 2008. At 1100 square feet, this 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom wing of a larger home includes a living and dining room combo, kitchen, oversized bedroom, bathroom, and private backyard with a picnic table. We also run another Airbnb (Bader Suite Flagstaff), and the two are connected by a door that remains locked at all times (it is keyed on both sides). If you are a larger group renting both units, let us know, and we can leave the door unlocked for you. We live in the main section of the house. While the apartment is on ground level, note that there are 3 steps inside the space. Flagstaff is a dark sky city, allowing for some of the best stargazing, so our neighborhood is quite dark at night. ENTRANCE: We provide our guests with one covered parking spot in our carport. Additional vehicles may park in our large driveway, and we can accommodate RVs, Uhauls, and other large vehicles. The entrance has a keypad for an easy self-check-in process! Once through, you will find an entry bench, a closet with hangers, and a rack to hang skis and snowboards if you are visiting our local ski resort. LIVING AND DINING ROOM: The living area contains a large sectional sofa and a dining table, both accommodating 6 people comfortably. A 50” TV sits over the fireplace with access to Netflix, HBO, Hulu, Sling, and Amazon Prime. The living room also contains a thermostat to run the gas heater that powers only your unit so that you can control the temperature for maximum comfort.KITCHEN: Just off the living room is your full kitchen (no dishwasher). It contains a reverse-osmosis, alkaline water drinking system. We have a flock of chickens in the backyard, so depending on availability, we will provide complimentary eggs. The kitchen is equipped with all your typical cooking accessories and dishware. A coffee bar contains a coffee maker, French press, coffee bean grinder, electric kettle, tea infusers, milk frother, and mixing spoons. Coffee beans, chai tea, cream, and sugar are also provided. BEDROOM: Just through the kitchen, you will find an oversized bedroom. The bedroom contains a queen bed (sleeping 2), plus two twin-over-twin bunk beds (sleeping 2 each). All beds have memory foams mattresses and personal night lights. Additionally, you’ll find a desk, full-size mirror, and a rod with hangers. Blackout curtains are hung over every window.BATHROOM: The spacious bathroom contains double sinks and a tub/shower combo. Additionally, it includes a washer and dryer that you are welcome to use. Laundry detergent, toiletries, towels, and hairdryer are provided. BACKYARD: You may enter into your private yard either through the living room or bedroom. The beautifully landscaped yard contains a picnic table and string lights, making a perfect gathering spot for morning coffee or nighttime stargazing. It also contains a gas grill for you to cook up anything you’d like. Just beyond the backyard, feel free to look at our flock of chickens! While we don’t allow guests inside their fenced run for safety (we have a mean rooster who attacks any human in sight), you can walk right up to the fence and watch them.OTHER BENEFITS: The space contains a few games. A mesh Wi-Fi system provides strong connectivity throughout the house. We do our best to accommodate anything you may need, so just ask! OTHER CONSIDERATIONS:NOISE: We do our best to keep noise to a minimum, and provide earplugs to help you sleep in! Note that we have 2 small dogs who enjoy barking. Our rooster usually starts crowing at sunrise, which is 5am in the summer. Additionally, we run a second Airbnb on the property and the two units share a wall. AC: Like most of Flagstaff, there is no air conditioning, but the house stays cool year-round. Both doors leading into the backyard contain screen doors so we recommend using those at night during the warmer months. We also leave a tower fan in the closet.LOCATION: The last half mile to our property is a maintained dirt road. Additionally, we get quite a bit of snow in the winter. The county paves the roads, but there may be up to a 12-hour delay between snowfall and paving. We highly recommend four-wheel drive in winter and any car that can handle dirt roads in summer. Keep in mind that we are a 20-minute drive from downtown Flag, and a vehicle is pretty much required unless you plan to use Uber or Lyft.ACCESSIBILITY: Lastly, the space is not wheelchair accessible as there are a few steps inside the unit.In winter especially (late October - early April), we highly recommend opting into Airbnb’s optional travel insurance while booking. Sometimes the main roads into town close during heavy snowstorms for a few hours or even overnight, so this will ensure that you are covered if that happens!Coconino County Permit #STR-24-0160Guest accessGuests have access to their private living room, kitchen, bedroom, bathroom, and backyard.Other things to noteInterested in getting food delivered? Grubhub services our neighborhood!

listing_description: Welcome to Vista A Frame!Perched high in the towering pines of Kachina Village, less than 15 minutes to downtown Flagstaff & 25 to the base of Snowbowl ski mountain. A cozy & moody retreat to come home to after a day of adventure & exploring the town. Sitting on a mountainside sprawled on half an acre, enjoy breakfast with this view right from the private back deck built high in the air. *Currently not allowing petsRecently renovated, the cabin has been updated with modern day luxuries while still keeping a cozy mountain cabin feel. Fully stocked kitchen, all new appliances and a gourmet coffee bar that includes a new Moccamaster coffee maker, Nespresso machine and French press. Coffee, creamer, sugar and pods provided. The A frame has a spacious upstairs loft accessed by a spiral staircase where the primary bedroom is located. Wake up in a Tuft & Needle king sized bed to the dreamiest view through its floor to ceiling windows. A sofa bed turns in to a full size bed for additional sleeping space. A Casaluna mattress topper is available for use with the sofa bed for an even more comfortable sleep.Downstairs is the second bedroom, with a queen T&N mattress. A new remote controlled gas fireplace will keep you cozy while drinking your morning coffee. The cabin also has new central heating furnace to make sure it is nice and warm throughout the night. A new minisplit AC installed for the warmer summer days to ensure comfort. The cabin has 1 full bathroom downstairs which was fully remodeled & stocked with essentials. Fast 350MB+ internet for movie streaming & in case you need to connect for work using the office space in the loft. The cabin is at the very end of a cul-de-sac in the quiet neighborhood of Kachina Village. Very private location with no drive thru traffic. Truly the best of both worlds as you are so close to town, and just far enough where you feel deep in the mountains. A perfect getaway for a peaceful retreat, or a couples stay. The highway is quickly accessed 2 minutes from the cabin which is very convenient and a corner store down the street that has produce, medicine, spirits and anything you might have forgotten for your stay. The space is ideal for 4 adults, due to the open loft and high decks it may not be a great fit for small children, or people looking to party (4 guests maximum). We do have neighbors who are full time residents, and care about ensuring the neighborhood remains peaceful for them as well. Please plan accordingly. Outdoor Space The A frame sits on a half acre lot. There are 2 large decks that were just rebuilt. The rear one is equipped with an outdoor table, propane fire pit, comfy lounge seating (stored in time of inclement weather) and a new propane bbq grill. Surrounded by hiking trails that are within walking distance & the beautiful Kachina Wetlands, it is the perfect place for outdoor lovers. The property benefits from its proximity to the highway which can result in a faint and distant sound of occasional cars when outside, not too noticeable. A parking pad in front of the cabin has enough room for 2 vehicles, please be mindful of the space with neighbors. Accessing the entrance does require going down a couple steps. Currently not allowing pets.Guest accessGuests will have full access to the cabin and backyard.Other things to noteWe do get snow in the winter months and while the city does a great job at plowing the roads it is highly recommended to watch the weather and ideally have chains, AWD or 4x4 if there will be snow throughout your stay. *PLEASE NOTE:* Our cabin is not considered child friendly. If you are interested in staying with children, please be aware of the following hazards: An open loft with railing. A narrow spiral staircase that does not have a baby gate. Furniture that is not mounted to the wall and may tip over Freestanding fireplace Outlets without covers. By requesting to book, you agree to full responsibility and liability for all children present during your stay and agree that they will be monitored by a responsible adult at all times.

This is to cover the time and gas of our cleaners sending out at the post office. **We are not flexible with check in and checkout times. It is a strict 11am or earlier checkout and 3pm or later check in.***Snow in Flagstaff Arizona. People love to visit Northern Arizona for its cooler temperatures in the summer and playing in the snow in the winter. We feel lucky to live here and like getting to share this with you, but snow in the winter can cause some logistical obstacles. As hosts, we will do our very best to keep pathways and driveways clear for guests, but it's not uncommon for Flagstaff to receive a foot or two of snow in a short period of time and this makes snow removal a challenge. Snow does create some obstacles for hosts and guests alike, so we want to be sure guests can know what to expect from us during the snowier times of year and what we in return ask of our guests.1) Guests can expect that prior to their arrival the driveway and paths to the home have been cleared at some point during the day of their arrival. However, if the driveway is plowed in the morning and more snow falls between morning time and check in you may arrive to the day's accumulation of snow on the drive. Guests can either drive over the snow or clear the snow with shovels provided. We are only able to do snow removal once a day. We do our very best to time our snow removal at the end of storms, but it doesn't always work out that way.2) THE BERMS! Any and every Flagstaff or Williams resident dreads the berm removal. What is the berm? The berm is a pile of snow at the end of your driveway caused by the snowplows pushing the snow from the streets to the side. There is nothing worse than shoveling your entire driveway only to have the plow come by and make a big berm you now have to clear before you can leave. We ALL dread the berm. As hosts we have NO WAY of knowing when the plows will come by. Because of this, it is possible that guests will arrive to a cleared driveway with a Berm at the end. If this happens guests will need to either drive over the berm (vehicle dependent) or use the provided shovels to make enough of an entry for your car to get through. Our snow removal crew will be around within the next 24 hours to take care of the rest. We are not a hotel with full time snow removal, so should you arrive during a snowstorm please know we are doing our best.3) Finally, something we love about Flagstaff is the sun after the snow, BUT this does mean the snow melts during the day and the wet turns into ice at night. We have a bucket with ice melt our guests are welcome to use on icy areas. Please only use it if there is ice as the salt is not good for the cement and trees. Also use sparingly as a little salt goes a long way and destroys the concrete if too much is used. Please please do not use more than a light dusting on the ice.

property_address: Entire cabin in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Located on the east side of Flagstaff this cabin is within the city limits, all the conveniences of home, yet has the rustic charm of a woodsy cabin. Walk out the front door to enjoy the hiking trails of Mount Elden, the Arizona Trail and Picture Canyon Trail. A great jumping-off point for your trips to the Grand Canyon, Sedona, Antelope Canyon, Wupatki National Monument, Walnut Canyon and all that Northern Arizona has to offer!The spaceWe have this listed for up to 4 people but it would be very tight accommodations for more than two or three adults. This is a small one-bedroom cabin. There is a daybed w/trundle in the living area and a comfortable queen in the bedroom Please note, there is no smoking allowed in the house but there has been smoking in the past; there are no pets allowed in the house but there have been pets in the house in the past. This guesthouse, located on the property of our primary residence, is often used by family members who have severe respiratory issues; for this reason absolutely no animals or smoking are permitted in the cabin.The house is in a residential neighborhood close to Highway 89, but it is set back, off the road, with views of Mount Elden and Sheep Hill. While the cabin is small-ish, it has a nice covered porch which adds additional three-season living space.There is a small stacked washer dryer set. It is adequate for light loads of approximately 10 lb, if you have heavy items please use the laundromat at the park Santa Fe Shopping Center.There is Wi-Fi (wireless) internet in the cabin, while we subscribe to the best service available to our location; in the town of Flagstaff internet outages can occur without notice , it is possible that internet may not be available at times. Speed and availability of Internet service is not guaranteed. Cable television is available through an online streaming service on a Roku streaming device. You can login to your personal streaming accounts on the Roku, there is also an auxiliary HDMI port if you want to connect your streaming device. We also get five or six broadcast channels over the antenna. I would say most houses in Flagstaff do not have air conditioning, but we do get some warm afternoons.....For this reason, we install a small window air conditioner in the cabin during the summer months. This will keep the bedroom comfortable on those days when it gets a little hot.In a couple of the photos you may see a wood daybed and a gas stove in the background. As a result of great guest input we have opted to swap these items out. The wood daybed has been replaced with a new daybed and the gas stove has been removed in favor of an electric stove.We are approximately 2 miles away from Flagstaff Mall, Safeway/Starbucks, Harkins Theaters, and other shopping. We are approximately 15 minutes down Route 66 from downtown Flagstaff and Northern Arizona University. We are approximately an hour and 15 minutes down Highway 89 from the Desert View Visitor Center at the south rim of the Grand Canyon. I personally prefer entering the Park from this entrance because the flow of traffic is generally lighter when starting from the East entrance. We are approximately 2 hours from Antelope Canyon. This cabin is also an excellent jumping-off point if you're going to make the trip to the north rim of the canyon.The fireplace you see in the pictures is not operable, the chimney is blocked off and insulated; no fires are permitted in the fireplace.Guest accessThere are two wood fence rails with red reflectors mounted to them by the entrance to the cabin please park here. It is important to never block other residents access to their homes for even a moment.Other things to noteOur family calls this The Shepherd's Cabin, it is located between Mount Elden and Sheep Hill on the east side of Flagstaff. What we have been able to find by word of mouth is that this cabin was built in the late 1800s as a temporary residence for Shepherds who were tending flocks in the area; at the time this was far removed from the town of Flagstaff. It has been nicely updated but still features the rustic charm of a well-built fieldstone cabin. Our friends and family have enjoyed staying here through the years and we are thrilled to offer it to those looking for unique and historic lodging through Airbnb. Please check out all the pictures, read the description and don't hesitate to write with any questions! Thank you Ed and Dawn

Fire dangers are in place for our safety. Obey them. Only have a fire in the 1 firepit out the front door. Do not create more. Be reasonable, 3 log max. Never have a fire in the wind. property_address: Tiny home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Come stay in our tiny cabin at our sustainable off-grid homestead! Enjoy lots of wildlife and unlimited hiking at nearby Abineau Canyon, Reese Canyon, Arizona Trail passage 34 aztrail .org, Bismarck Lake, Red Mountain, Grand Canyon(50 mins) and many more! This area is a top destination for fall colors, hiking, bird watching, wildlife, and reconnecting! Secluded location 18 miles north of Flagstaff surrounded by national forest.The spaceOur family has worked hard to re-establish the 1800’s Potato Ranch Homestead so you can come experience history, nature and a touch of farm life completely off the grid! We lived in this off-grid 392 sqft cabin for 3 years while we built our dream farmhouse up the hill to provide the best and freshest to our growing family. We’re so happy to get to share it with you and your family! While you’re here you’ll be surrounded by Coconino National Forest! There are so many things to explore… springs, valleys, rock climbing, foraging, volcanic sites, Native American ruins, Grand Canyon, hiking, dirt biking, 4 wheeling, cross country skiing, and more. While you’re relaxing in the cool mountain air at the cabin, you can enjoy the outdoor dining, propane grill, propane fire pit, tree swing, and nature. Watch the garden grow, the animals graze, gorgeous sunsets and night skies. Observe the elk, deer, and occasional antelope come to get a drink at our nearby pond. We do have 2 big dogs to watch over our farm animals. There are games, books and toy box upstairs in the loft for your enjoyment as well as two queen sized beds and pack n play. All our fabrics are high quality natural fibers! Chilly night? Cozy up by the wood heat stove with a cup of something warm, put a puzzle together or just chat with your special people to reconnect. Speaking of connection we are not sorry that there is no WiFi here. It’s a distraction to our families and we are here to connect with them…not the world. You’ll find there is poor cell service here but if you need, just head back toward the highway and you’ll have all the signal you need. Verizon service seems to do quite well with most guests able to call, text, and use the Airbnb app. I’ll provide my cell phone number for any questions, or needs you have during your stay. You’ll be able to text me :-) We are located in hunting unit 7 EAST and are 5 miles off highway 180 on a dirt road. Some sections are not maintained so we suggest a moderate clearance vehicle, although many people are happy with a sedan. We DO Require 4WD in snowy weather or early spring mud (March and April esp). Remember we are Off-Grid and we also haul water so please be conservation minded and be nice to our planet by taking short showers. Sometimes we have guests with special health needs. I’m happy to accommodate you but, send me a request/inquiry before you book to make sure it’s a good fit! Lastly remember we rely completely on solar batteries so if you are a night-owl who stays up all night running things that require electric (lights, water) this unit won’t fit your needs well.Guest accessThe open grassy area near the cabin and the swing are there for you to enjoy. The pasture behind the cabin is for our grazing animals. Please do not enter the pasture with animals or feed them.Driving info: there are dirt roads to our place and while we drive a Camry and small cars, if you aren’t confident with off-road travel and how to place your tires, arrange for a higher riding vehicle. It’s a beautiful drive!Other things to noteNo smoking tobacco, marijuana, etc inside the cabin.Enjoy watching the peaceful farm animals but don’t feed them or pick them up. Clifford is our livestock guardian dog. He will greet you when you arrive. In the cold months please know that the heat source is the wood stove. I’m happy to show you how to use it. Our solar system can’t handle space heaters, insta-pots, etc. Also please dont enter the green house or pick up/chase the chickens. Thanks so much! :-)

Our house is located on 3 acres right at the base of the Snowbowl ski resort, making it the ideal location for winter ski trips. Just a little over an hour from the Grand Canyon (only 3 stop signs!), adventure awaits year-round. Enjoy the wildlife (elk, many birds, etc), incredible stargazing, trails, and more.The spaceLocated off the beaten path, this historic house was home to Lou Bader, a local figure of whom the neighborhood was named after, until his passing in 2008. At 350+ square feet, this private master suite with outdoor patio is a great home-base for all of your northern Arizona adventures. We also run another Airbnb (Bader Guest House Flagstaff), and the two are connected by a door that remains locked at all times (it is keyed on both sides). If you are a larger group renting both units, let us know, and we can leave the door unlocked for you. We live in the main section of the house, which shares a wall with this space. While the suite is on ground level, note that there is a step inside the space and 2 steps at the entrance. Flagstaff is a dark sky city, allowing for some of the best stargazing, so our neighborhood is quite dark at night. ENTRANCE: You will both park and enter around the back of the house. The entrance, a gate, has a keypad for an easy self-check-in process! Once through you will immediately see your own private, covered, outdoor patio with a gas grill plus an eating area. As you walk down further, you will see the sliding door to your private suite. There is a motion detector light right at the entrance to help you see the door at night. Because Flagstaff is a world renounced dark sky city with light restrictions, we are unable to leave any other lights on at night.BEDROOM W/ KITCHENETTE: As you enter through the sliding door with screen door, you will be in a large bedroom with a king-size bed and a memory foam mattress. Additionally, you’ll find a kitchenette and cozy eating area for two. The kitchenette includes a mini-fridge, microwave, toaster oven, coffee maker, hot plate, kettle, egg cooker, wine glasses, and other cooking utensils and cookery (no sink). It is great for very simple meals or heating food up, but not ideal for anything complex. Coffee and tea are provided, as well as a 2-gallon dispenser of reverse-osmosis alkaline water (which we will happily refill!). We have a flock of chickens in the backyard, so depending on availability, will provide complimentary eggs. The bedroom contains a 39” TV with access to Netflix, HBO, Hulu, Sling, and Amazon Prime, and blackout curtains allow for sleeping in. The door between the bedroom and main house remains locked at all times for complete privacy. NOOK: Just off the bedroom, separated by a curtain, you will find a nook holding twin size bunk beds, both with memory foam mattresses. You will also find a full-size mirror and a corner rod with hangers.BATHROOM: The bathroom contains double sinks and a spacious, glass wall shower (no tub). Toiletries, towels, and hairdryer are provided. PARKING: We have plenty of space for parking. We have a designated parking area right by your entrance that easily fits two cars, but if you'll be arriving with an RV, Uhaul, or more than two cars, please let us know ahead of time and we will direct you to a different area of our land to park comfortably in.CHICKENS: Find farm life fascinating? Feel free to check out our flock of backyard chickens! They are close to your entrance gate, and you drive right past them right before you park. While we don’t let guests inside their fenced run for safety (we have a mean rooster who attacks any human in sight), you can walk right up to the fence and watch them. Additionally, please do not feed them to protect their organic diet. Be careful not to stick your fingers in because the rooster will try and attack you through the fence. He’s one of the white ones, so be extra careful, especially with children!OTHER BENEFITS: The room contains a few games. Extra linens and towels will be provided upon request. A mesh Wi-Fi system provides strong connectivity. If you need anything else, just let us know and we’ll do our best to accommodate!OTHER CONSIDERATIONS: NOISE: We do our best to keep noise to a minimum, and provide earplugs to help you sleep in! There is also a white noise machine in the unit that drowns out most noise and is great to sleep with. Note that we have a toddler who is still learning to use her inside voice, and 2 small dogs who enjoy barking. Our rooster usually starts crowing at sunrise, which is 5am in the summer. Additionally, we run a second Airbnb on the property and the two units share a wall. Both units have a house rule of quiet hours after 10pm.AC: Like most of Flagstaff, there is no air conditioning. The house stays cool year-round (we regularly use the heater even in summer!). The room contains a space heater to help you regulate temperature. If the room does get a little warm, even with the ceiling and tower fans, the sliding door entrance contains a screen door to maintain a breeze.LOCATION: The last half mile to our property is a maintained dirt road. Additionally, we get quite a bit of snow in the winter. The county paves the roads, but there may be up to a 12-hour delay between snowfall and paving. We highly recommend four-wheel drive in winter and any car that can handle dirt roads in summer. Keep in mind that we are a 20-minute drive from downtown Flag, and a vehicle is pretty much required unless you plan to use Uber or Lyft.ACCESSIBILITY: Lastly, the space is not wheelchair accessible as there are two exterior steps and one inside the unit.In winter especially (late October - early April), we highly recommend opting into Airbnb’s optional travel insurance while booking. Sometimes the main roads into town close during heavy snowstorms for a few hours or even overnight, so this will ensure that you are covered if that happens!Coconino County Permit #STR-24-0160Guest accessGuests will have full access to the private bedroom with king size bed and kitchenette, nook with twin bunk beds, private en suite bathroom, and private outdoor patio. Guests are also welcome to walk around our 3-acre land.Other things to noteInterested in getting food delivered? Grubhub services our neighborhood!

property_address: Entire rental unit in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Our space is located in a beautiful and safe neighborhood in Flagstaff. Minutes away from NAU campus, The Flagstaff airport, downtown, Snowbowl, Lake Mary, and many hiking or mountain biking trails. The Grand Canyon is just an hour and a half away and Sedona is a short 45 minute drive.The spaceOur space has a separate driveway and private entrance. Although connected to our home the space is completely private. You will have a full kitchen, bathroom and laundry. The bedroom has a queen size bed with a heated mattress pad. The gas fireplace will keep you nice and warm during your stay. No wood required just control the temp with the thermostat on the wall! At this time we do not have a great space for outdoor entertainment however we are close to many great trails and parks. We are a short dive from downtown Flagstaff with many shops and restaurants.Guest accessPlease take the gravel driveway up along the side of the house. Your private entrance is accessible with a code you will be given prior to your arrival. Your space is completely private! You may help yourself to whatever you need within the rental space. The backyard and play area are not included in the rental.Other things to noteOur backyard and the play equipment in it is not part of the rental. It is important to know that during winter months we can get heavy snowfall. We do our best to clear the driveway of snow as soon as possible, however 4 wheel drive or chains are recommended. We will not be responsible for stuck vehicles. We do not have a fire pit available to the rental and we do not allow outdoor fires on the property. Smoking is not permitted anywhere on the property. If any smell of cigarette smoke is detected within the unit you will be charged an extra cleaning fee of $100.00. This also includes the use of e-cigarettes and vape pens. If you are a smoker it is probably best to rent a different place. Our weather is beautiful most of the summer, however like many properties in Flagstaff we do not have air conditioning for the hot days. We do provide a window air conditioning unit that works well for the hot months. Usually July- August. The window unit is not installed year round and does not work well during rainy days. Fans are available year round and a nice cross breeze can be created by opening the front door, bolting the security door and opening the windows. The space is attached but separate from our home. This means that you will not share a space with us but there can be noise transfer. We do our very best to be mindful of our noise but you will likely hear us from time to time.

property_address: Entire cabin in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: While not technically a treehouse, this log cabin is 79 steps up, sits above ground level and is surrounded by ponderosa pines! Once inside this cozy and peaceful home, you'll feel like you're in your own private treehouse. Located in Kachina Village, just 8 miles south of downtown Flagstaff, you'll get to enjoy dark skies and quiet evenings while also being close to the city center. Please note that you DO have to climb all 79 steps and cross a foot bridge over Pumphouse Wash.The spaceThis is a one bedroom, one bathroom log cabin that sits high up in the Ponderosa Pines in Kachina Village, just south of Flagstaff. Guests must cross a foot bridge and climb 79 steps to access the house. Once inside, you'll find a peaceful and cozy space. We have a gas fireplace that turns on automatically with the thermostat settings to keep you extra warm. The bedroom is in a large loft above the living room and kitchen (guests must climb another small ladder with handrails to get up there). The bathroom is large and also holds the large LG washer and dryer units. The open kitchen has stainless steel appliances, a new gas range, and a bar top with four stools. The living room has a small wrap-around couch, tv with firestick to use your own subscriptions, and a DVD player if you'd like to bring any or rent from the Redbox down the street. We also have a ton of DVD’s for your use. Finally, the large deck provides a view into the trees and the wildlife that frequents them as well as Pumphouse Wash. The deck is a great place for reading, lounging, enjoying a cozy drink on a summer evening, and outdoor cooking (propane grill and tank included). This is an awesome house for two guests (will entertain the idea of more depending on the situation) looking for a unique experience in a gorgeous setting. It's close to trails, a playground/park, a riparian area, 5 miles to Fort Tuthill County Park (music venue, rodeo venue, county fair, Flagstaff Extreme Course, FREE bike park, trails, picnicking, etc ), 9 miles to downtown Flagstaff and 23 miles to the Arizona Snowbowl.Guest accessPrivate 1-2 car parking space along the street. Guests then cross the foot bridge and go up 79 steps. We suggest guests not bring heavy suitcases.Other things to noteWe have a contracted snow removal person who plows and shovels post storm. He does the driveway and all 79 steps. There are also snow shovels for your use during any storms.

property_address: Entire home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: The Fortress is your sweet mountain oasis! Perfect for all types of trips: small family excursion, couple’s getaway, international adventures and everything in between. Minutes from excellent dining & entertainment in Historic Downtown, quick access to Snowbowl & NAU, pleasant drive’s distance from Sedona & the Grand Canyon, and a stone’s throw from forest trails, parks and the local grocery store. You'll love this private peaceful space. Looking forward to serving you here at The Fortress!The spaceYou will love this space! Our lovely walkout basement apartment offers a warm living/dining combo room, private bathroom, kitchenette, and beautiful bedroom.BEDROOM - A modern and warmly decorated room with a lush queen bed, ceiling fan, personal desk, dresser, TV with Netflix and Hulu ready to go, iron & ironing board, two comfy bath robes, and plenty of closet space!MAIN ROOM – The apartment is entered through the main room. This space offers an intimate dining table for 4 (if more table space is needed, there is a foldable card table and 4 folding chairs in the closet). The living room also bodes a cozy and romantic wood-burning stove fireplace perfect for an evening in after a long day of adventures! Firewood will be provided; we just ask that you be responsible (fire extinguisher is in the closet if things get out of hand☺). The couch is super comfy and can sleep one. There is plenty of floor space as well for the queen-size air mattress being stored in the hallway closet. KITCHENETTE – You will also have a kitchenette with a full fridge stocked with bubbly water, bottled water, a filtered water pitcher, and coffee creamer. We also offer a microwave, toaster oven, hot plate, electric kettle, French press with coffee, tea & hot chocolate provided, and dishes & utensils for dining & cooking. If extra water is needed, Flagstaff tap water is wonderful – it's what everyone drinks up here! The kitchen sink has a garbage disposal whose switch is under the countertop to the right of the sink.BATHROOM – Simple and clean bathroom with a full tub and shower. Extra towels, shampoo, conditioner, soap, shaving cream & razor, toothpaste & toothbrush, hair dryer, and other bathroom products will be available for those who like to travel light. Perhaps most importantly, for those who enjoy a leisurely experience, the two bathrobes hanging in the bedroom closet are at your disposal! EXTRA STUFF - Extra linens, blankets, pillows, towels, wash clothes, first aid kit, games, chairs, and fan are all housed in the hallway and living room closets.Guest accessYour private entrance is located under the upper deck as you walk up the driveway; you’ll know because it’s the BROWN door! We live upstairs, so your door is yours. The whole place is yours with the exception of 2 doors in the hallway and 1 in the kitchen that you won't have access to (those are just closets) and a bi-fold door in the wall, which allows us to access the rental when it's not booked. You are free to park on the street or in the driveway in the parking spot to the furthest left labeled #1.Other things to noteThe space is on the bottom floor of our family home. We work hard to ensure that you enjoy as much peace and quiet as possible, you will likely hear us at some point, unfortunately. With that said, we are out of the house most mornings by 8 AM. We are usually all asleep by 9 PM on most nights, you're welcome to come and go as you please whenever though, we are not disturbed by any activity downstairs. My mother also lives with us and is extremely quiet and respectful. She is almost always available if you need any immediate help.We believe that what we have should be shared with those who don't, so we will be donating a percentage of our nightly fees to non-profits and charities that are near to our hearts.The current non-profit is "Sage Home" in Flagstaff.

property_address: Entire cabin in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Hike/ Bike Trails .2miGrand Canyon 90 / Sedona 45This gorgeous A-frame offers a large fenced back yard, plenty of light, and amenities to make your stay memorable. Recently remodeled with 3 bedrooms and 1 1/2 baths. This gem has a full stocked kitchen, amazing backyard, fire pit, grill and plenty of space to play. Dog friendly with a $50 nonrefundable pet fee, child friendly, family friendly. Quiet neighborhood cabin in the woods, yet so close to Flagstaff! Don’t miss out! Permit#: STR-23-0160The spaceThis property is beautiful with tall, majestic pine trees to provide wonderful shade while outdoors! The neighborhood is quaint and quiet with friendly neighbors!You will enter into the beautiful living area with new leather seating and log furniture, for gathering to chat, play games, watch movies, or watch Roku! We offer free Wifi as well! The large windows at the front of the cabin will give you plenty of natural lighting. The fully stocked, remodeled kitchen offers plenty of space for more than one cook, bar height seating and an open concept for great entertaining space. You will be supplied with dish towels, fresh sponge, basic supplies such as oil, spices and salt and pepper. All dish soaps, handsoap, paper towels will also be provided. A short hall leads to the Queen room which has an en suite powder room. Across the hall, you will find a futon that opens up for sleeping. The full bathroom sits between these two rooms and is fully stocked with shampoo, conditioner and soap in the shower. You will find we offer more so you can pack less. property_address: Entire home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Park on the premises, walk 2 blocks to the heart of Historic Downtown Flagstaff. Cozy one bedroom house affectionately called 'Hobbit House' for having low ceilings, especially in the bathroom (see description for details), queen bed, well stocked kitchen, private front porch. HOBBIT HOUSE is over 100 years old and is about 500 Sq Ft. It has low ceilings (maybe people were shorter back then) which are about 7 feet high with the exception of the bathroom which has a 6' 3" high ceiling. Also, time has settled the house so the floors are a bit uneven. So if you are a tall person or need to spread out keep this in mind. These characters of this older well loved home make it unique and cozy. Provided is one off-street PARKING for a small to medium size vehicle. The BEDROOM is small with a queen bed, closet and dresser for your belongings. The BATHROOM has a very comfortable and original claw tub with shower. The ceiling of the bathroom is not very high (6'3" high, one of the special characters of this home!). I am 5’3” tall and standing in the tub to take a shower, I need to bend my knees to rinse off my hair as the shower head is a few inches lower than the ceiling. If you are 5’8” tall and standing in the tub for a shower, your head will touch the ceiling. The claw tub measures at the top about 2 feet wide and about 4 1/2 feet long and is quite comfortable having the right curvature for laying back and relaxing in a nice hot bath. Adding Epsom salts (provided) and relaxing after a long day of traveling, hiking, walking, or shopping can be a very rewarding experience. Plenty of quality towels and wash rags, variety of hand and hair soaps, body lotion, hair dryer and miscellaneous toiletries should you have forgotten something.The kitchen sink just outside the door of the bathroom is the one sink for both the kitchen and bathroom.The KITCHEN is equipped with a gas stove/oven, microwave oven, refrigerator, a Mr. Coffee 12 cup coffee maker, electric kettle, full set of quality pots and pans, dishes, knives and silverware, plus glasses for adult beverages. A Brita filter is also provided but Flagstaff water is pretty good to drink right out of the tap. Also provided are a variety of teas (black, green and herbal), coffee, sugar, cream, basic spices, olive oil and balsamic vinegar. I have tried to think of all the basic things needed for preparation of most simple meals but if there is anything you need, just ask me.There are many local shops selling a variety of beer and wine within minutes of walking that I could direct you to, some are bars so will be open late. Or bring your favorite with you and enjoy in the comfort of this pleasant space!LIVING ROOM has a full size couch, desk and gas heater with a fireplace window to enjoy the cool nights in comfort in the winter months and lots of books on the surrounding country in which to explore. To protect the floors I ask that you remove your shoes at the door please. I have provided many pairs of slippers for your enjoyment should you not have brought your own.OUTSIDE, relax in one of 2 spaces for your use. The front porch is very private, faces east so enjoyable with your morning coffee or tea watching the world go by and shady in the evenings to enjoy a delightful beverage during the warmer months. The back yard faces south so gets the afternoon sun and is fenced and semi-private as my other one bedroom Airbnb is close by.THERE IS NO TV AND NO AIR CONDITIONING in the home. Plenty of fans are provided during the summer months.Guest accessI will meet you upon your arrival and take you into the house, give a short orientation of the space and give you keys. In the rare occasion that I will not be able to meet you, I will let you know and make sure you get keys.Other things to noteFlagstaff can cool down at nights so bring enough covering to be comfortable in the evening hours and do remember we are at 7,000 feet, which takes time to adjust to this elevation for some. We keep it simple so you can afford to enjoy our 5 star community and the beauty that surrounds us. Our space is clean and comfortable. Relax in the cozy nook with tea and a book. Didn't bring one? Select something from our little library. Play a record! Make music. Watch a classic movie. And please enjoy the art! One of us is a local photographer and we are both avid adventurers!The spaceOur place is a brand newly remodeled casita. It's small with lots of light. It stays warm and sits in a beautiful garden space in the Spring. There is no reliable wireless. There is also no air conditioning. We mitigate this by opening windows at night and closing them during the day. Day and night in a mountain town can vary by 30-40 degrees. We often see temps in the 80’s on Summer days and 40 degree nights.Guest accessGuests have access to the whole building.Other things to noteIn that Winter months, you’re limited to one driveway parking space. In the Summer months, street parking is available. We have no reliable wireless internet for guest access. We do not have air conditioning and June is a very hot month as we wait for monsoon’s to begin. It is recommended that you open the windows at night and shut them during the day. This is how most locals keep their houses cool.

property_address: Entire cabin in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: This AFrame cabin in Kachina Village was recently renovated inside & out. We've tried to create a quality stay, that feels comfortable & familiar. During the process we had four words represent our design mantra - "cozy, modern, vintage, grandma." We hope you feel a bit of each, but most importantly we hope you feel rested and rejuvenated after you "simplystay". Follow us @ simplystayframeTwo separate floors. Exterior stairs only between living/loft & downstairs bedroom.PETS ARE NOT ALLOWEDThe spaceCompletely renovated and reconstructed interior and deck. Designed to make the small spaces feel big. Styled with a mix of textures, colors, patterns and finishes to compliment and accentuate.SimplyStayFrame is located in Kachina Village - the perfect location to explore all that Northern AZ has to offer. Less than 20 minutes south of downtown, historic Flagstaff - with breweries, bars, and a number of delicious dining options. Just 45 minutes from Arizona Snowbowl Ski Resort. Hiking and biking in the summers - snowboarding and skiing in the winter - and scenic Gondola rides all year round. Only 45 minutes north of Sedona, drive the beautiful 89A freeway and swim in Oak Creek Canyon. Get up early and make a day of easy access to the Grand Canyon's South Rim (1.5 hrs) or Lake Powell (2.5 hrs).Multiple hiking trails within walking distance. Dollar General and Shell Gas Station (with Subway) easily accessible. Drive over to Mountainaire (5 minutes) for additional hiking, local tavern and country store.Main Level: Up the exterior stairs to the large deck, with full dining table. In to the main level, you'll find the shared living space. The classic "A" architecture highlighted by cedar ceilings. Featured items include sofa with bumper and pull out sleeper, original wood burning oven and a 50" LG SmartTV. New kitchen opens up to living room to keep family and friends connected. Comfortable dining for six with custom upholstery and laundry room as you head back toward the bathroom. Bathroom features marble vanity and soaking tub. Up the spiral staircase and to the loft with a queen-sized, Tuft & Needle mattress. Downstairs: A second bedroom with a queen-sized T&N bed. Full bathroom with walk-in shower, small closet and additional coffee pot allow guests a comfortable stay. Downstairs bedroom is accessible via a private entrance. Must use deck stairs (outside) to go up/down from main level.Permit: STR-23-0334Guest accessPrivate entrance all accessible via keypad entry. Shared "driveway" with neighbor, please stay to the right. Parking is on an incline. We do recommend using your parking brake and encourage using an AWD vehicle, if possible. The walk from your vehicle to front patio/deck can be icy during winter, please take your time and walk carefully.Other things to noteThis property does not have an air conditioner, but does have central heat (furnace). There is a ceiling fan and multiple windows that open. Temps tend to stay a touch cooler compared to the city, as we are located in a small canyon. The stairs up to the loft are narrow and steep. Each step has grip tape for your safety, please take your time and watch your step.There is no smoking inside the cabin. While we currently have a no pet policy for our guests, we are dog owners ourselves. The space is professionally cleaned after we visit and we take great care to reduce any sign of their stay. While you may get lucky and find some firewood left behind from a guest's stay, we do recommend grabbing firewood and starters from a local gas station or grocer. The smaller the logs, the better!

listing_description: Come enjoy this quiet little home only 10 miles east of Flagstaff. Spacious and comfortable, private space with parking. We updated our internet provider and our wifi system in February 2019 so we can provide good service to our guests.You may see deer or elk on the property in the mornings or evenings, and if you enjoy watching/seeing birds, we have a wide variety all year long.In addition to the queen bed in the bedroom and the queen sofa bed in the living room, there is a single bed roll-away available on request and a Pack n Play crib. The Airbnb "guest house" is located on 5 acres with the right next door in the main house.Guest accessThe house is self-contained, with no shared amenities or areas except the driveway. We have a little heeler dog named Josie - she is friendly, but may bark some, especially when you arrive. The neighbors also have friendly dogs, but they don't visit much.please be aware and respectful of the speed limit. This is a quiet neighborhood on a private road. There are children playing, animals, and horseback riders. please be respectful and careful on the road.Please park to the right of the Airbnb house - we put up solar lights so it is easy to see the parking area.The house is single story, with access at ground level (no steps).Other things to noteWe do not allow pets at Yetta's House, and no smoking of any kind in the house.We can easily adjust the heat/air conditioning to your needs. Let us know if it is too warm or too cool in the house, and we will set the temperatures to meet your needs.During the warmer months, we will have the cooling on. in general, we will set the cooling at 76 degrees. Let us know if this is ok for you or if you need the cooling or set differently for your needs.There is a gas "woodstove" in the living room that is for decoration only and does not work.The hot tub is available year-round. We ask our guests to shower before entering the hot tub to keep the water clean and clear and to minimize our use of chemicals.Also, the train tracks are about 1 1/2 mile from the house, and you can hear the horns sometimes. It may bother you at night, especially if you have the windows open. Some guests love it, others don't.

property_address: Yurt in Sedona, Arizona, United States
listing_description: 🏜Immerse yourself in nature with the comforts of home! We have a cozy Lotus Belle tent set up just for you with a king-size organic mattress and open-air bathroom. Our hope is that you can relax into the beauty and magic of this deeply sacred place.There simply is not a more magical+beloved place in all of Sedona. While this spot has visitors during the day, you get the unique experience of evenings here alone at the creek with the moon+stars+Cathedral Rock. The mornings are truly glorious!The space🏜 Cathedral Rock is one of the most powerful vortex spots in Sedona, and this place here on Oak Creek with the view of Cathedral Rock, called Red Rock Crossing, is perhaps the most famous place in all of Sedona. There is only one property right on the creek with the direct view of Cathedral Rock - and this is it. The view from our back yard is the most photographed image in all of the American Southwest. This is where people come to get married, to pray, to be in contemplation, and to rest deeply in the beauty and majesty of the Earth. I am the newest stewardess of this land, and love this place with all my heart. It is my honor and joy to share this extraordinary, exquisite land with you. We ask that those who come refrain from loud music or any excessive drinking, and to join us in respecting the sanctity of this land.In the summer months (May-Sep), there is an A/C to keep you cool. In the winter, the Belle is super cozy and warm. It is insulated with a special insulator called the “Cocoon”, and we have an electric infrared fireplace and an electric heating blanket under (Nov-Feb). People love it in the winter. Plus we have heat cables running on the water lines so you can have a nice hot shower under our rain head shower even when it’s cold out. :-)The main house is currently empty as we await to do remodeling (date TBD - don't worry - we won't have guests while we do the remodel).We do have guests that stay in the our cozy private studio on the property but they have their own facilities and you do not have to interact unless you want to. The only overlap/shared space is in the yard and common patio sitting area. There is enough space distinction that you will feel privacy and no overlap unless you want to.Guest accessYou have access to your luxury Lotus Bell tent and the outdoor bathroom. The bathroom is private with views of trees and has a retractable awning to keep out rain or snow. It is VERY IMPORTANT that only toilet paper goes in the toilet. We have a super sensitive septic system. We have a small trashcan for any feminine products etc. We do not have a kitchen for your use, however we do provide a small cooler for you to keep items in for your own use. (We ask that you please clean it out entirely when you leave.) Note: it's Sedona so there are javelinas - little pigs. We recommend NOT leaving food out, so please put it away. We do provide water, coffee, tea, tea kettle, and a small tea table. You can park in our house driveway. Food and restaurants are nearby in town, about 10 minute drive and I provide a list of all my recommendations.Other things to noteNote: A Lotus Belle is a "glamping" tent. :-) Because it gets cold in the evenings, we have special insulation in the cooler months to keep you warm, along with duvet and blankets, a heated blanket, and an electric fireplace. Guests have always stayed plenty warm in the winter. In the summer months, we provide a fan and A/C.We only have parking for one vehicle. Unfortunately, there is no room for trailers! Let us know if you need a solution for this as occasionally we may be able to sort something. Our amazing place backs up to national forest land and Crescent Moon Ranch Park. During daytime in summer (Saturdays and Sundays), there are quite a few visitors enjoying the creek, as the area really is a rare gem in all of Sedona. Evenings after 8pm it is usually empty and you get to enjoy solitude of the Sedona vortex. During weekdays, people come and go along the creek and it is fairly uncrowded. Also, as mentioned earlier – we do have a small studio on the property that we rent out to guests visiting Sedona. There is enough separation between the studio and yurt, as they are on the opposite side of the property as the studio. The only overlap between the two is the driveway area, and the backyard couch sitting area that is shared. (The majority of the house and the rooms directly behind the Belle tent are completely unoccupoied as I live offsite and await renovations in the upcoming year.Also of high importance - do not spray ANY perfume, bug spray or light incense in the Belle. The fumes stick around and are very hard to get rid of. This could cause health issues for other guests. We provide detailed instructions on how to make your stay in the Lotus Belle cozy and comfortable. Check out the Guest Manual here on Airbnb when you book. We also have a small manual in the Belle. There cell coverage is not amazing unless you have Verizon or ATT (and even that is a little choppy.) We DO have wifi and will provide you with that password, wifi calls are not a problem.Lastly, please be mindful of the roots on the ground surrounding the property. There are many old-growth trees in this area, and some roots stick above the ground and is important to be detailed when watching your step!

property_address: Entire guest suite in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Unwind in the natural light and luxurious appointments of this modern studio nestled up to a city park and attached to our main house. Beautifully renovated and flooded with light, the spacious, open 375 sq ft is your perfect home-away-from-home for exploring the wonders of Flagstaff and northern AZ. Expected amenities like plush bedding, a fully-stocked kitchenette, and a smart TV combine with extra touches like laundry, a rainforest shower, relaxing shared patio, and 400 MB wi-fi. Welcome!The spaceThe open concept studio apartment attached to the main house opens into a living area with an L-shaped sleeper sofa and LED TV on one side, and a newly built, fully-stocked kitchenette and dining space on the other. At the far end of the studio is a new queen size bed and dedicated workspace, all bathed in natural light by multiple windows and a large skylight in the center of the apartment. Please note that the wall with the sofa and bed is shared with our main house, and while insulated, is not fully soundproof - you may occasionally hear our kids, dogs, or TV.The door next to the kitchen leads to a large, luxurious newly-remodeled bathroom with a huge rainforest shower, brand new stacking washer and dryer, and walk-in closet.Outside the apartment is a spacious, well-furnished, shaded patio shared with the host family, including a dining table, sofa, hammock swing, fire pit, and gas grill (and two pet bunnies).The property backs up to a wonderful city park, accessible through a public entrance just a short walk down our street.Guest accessAccess to the space is down the driveway of the property and through the patio door using the smart lock code provided upon booking. The guest house shares an insulated wall with the back of our main house. The closed door in the living space is attached to the main house, and will remain locked at all times, as will one storage closet off the bathroom. While we have made every effort to insulate and reduce sound to the studio, we do have kids and dogs, and you may occasionally hear them inside or outside the house. With advance arrangements, use of the laundry room (washer/dryer) in the main house is available, especially for longer stays. Outside the apartment, the patio is a shared space for your enjoyment, and use of the gas grill or fire pit are available with advance arrangements with the hosts (and subject to local seasonal fire restrictions). For liability reasons, neither the garage, nor the back yard trampoline or tree fort should be accessed by guests. However, the city park behind our house offers amazing play equipment and recreational activities!Other things to noteArizona TPT License 21566022

property_address: Entire home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Welcome to our newly built home in Juniper Point located directly across from Flagstaff's premier golf community, Pine Canyon, and minutes from NAU. This home offers a unique blend of elegance and comfort, perfect for enjoying the cool pines of Flagstaff. Prepare delicious meals in our fully equipped kitchen with Wolf appliances and ample counter space. The separate studio offers additional space and privacy for guests.. The studio features an additional king-sized bed and a private bathroom.The spaceBeautiful, spacious home.Guest accessKeyless entry.Other things to notePeople love to visit Northern Arizona for its cooler temperatures in the summer and playing in the snow in the winter. We feel lucky to live here and like getting to share this with you, but snow in the winter can cause some logistical obstacles. As hosts, we will do our very best to keep pathways and driveways clear for guests, but it's not uncommon for Flagstaff to receive a foot or two of snow in a short period of time and this makes snow removal a challenge. Snow does create some obstacles for hosts and guests alike, so we want to be sure guests can know what to expect from us during the snowier times of year and what we in return ask of our guests.**Guests renting the studio only, please park on the right side of the driveway and garage. If renting only the main home, please park only on the left side of the driveway and garage.1) Guests can expect that prior to their arrival the driveway and paths to the home have been plowed at some point during the day of their arrival. However, if the driveway is plowed in the morning and more snow falls between morning time and check in you may arrive to the day's accumulation of snow on the drive. Guests can either drive over the snow or clear the snow with shovels provided. We only are able to do snow removal once a day. We do our very best to time our snow removal at the end of storms, but it doesn't always work out that way.2) THE BERMS! Any and every Flagstaff or Williams resident dreads the berm removal. What is the berm? The berm is a pile of snow at the end of your driveway caused by the snowplows pushing the snow from the streets to the side. There is nothing worse than shoveling your entire driveway only to have the plow come by and make a big berm you now have to clear before you can leave. We ALL dread the berm. As hosts we have NO WAY of knowing when the plows will come by. Because of this, it is possible that guests will arrive to a plowed driveway with a Berm at the end. If this happens guests will need to either drive over the berm (vehicle dependent) or use the provided shovels to make enough of an entry for your car to get through. Our snow removal crew will be around within the next 24 hours to take care of the rest. We are not a hotel with full time snow removal, so should you arrive during a snowstorm please know we are doing our best.3) Finally, something we love about Flagstaff is the sun after the snow, BUT this does mean the snow melts during the day and the wet turns into ice at night. We have a bucket with ice melt our guests are welcome to use on icy areas. Please only use it if there is ice as the salt is not good for the cement and trees. Also use sparingly as a little salt goes a long way.4) We offer landscaping services during the warmer months and snow removal during the colder months. Those services may happen during your stay. If you have any questions or concerns regarding someone on the property, please don't hesitate to reach out.

property_address: Entire rental unit in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: A beautiful new space in a 100-year-old home in the historic district of downtown Flagstaff! This upper level of the home has its own porch with views of the San Francisco Peaks and Mars Hill (Lowell Observatory), and a relaxing and spacious layout that can accommodate longer stays as well as short stopovers to adventure in Northern Arizona. Just a short couple blocks walk to all the downtown shops and restaurants.The spaceWelcome to our charming short-term rental property, nestled within a spacious 7-unit compound consisting of two homes. This particular unit is perched above the main house, boasting its own private entrance via an upper porch. Inside, you'll find a fully equipped kitchen complete with a dishwasher, refrigerator, coffee maker, and microwave. The separate bedroom features a brand-new mattress and fresh bedding for your comfort. Entertainment options abound with a Smart TV offering access to Netflix and other apps. The bathroom has been recently renovated, showcasing all-new fixtures, and you'll enjoy the convenience of heating and air conditioning. Plus, on-site parking awaits you just at the base of the exterior stairs. Whether you prefer bar seating or a spacious dining area, there are various options for you to feel right at home.While staying with us, you'll also have access to a shared backyard space, which is occasionally frequented by other guests and their dogs – all are welcome to enjoy it.The living area offers picturesque views framed by original restored windows. Here, you'll find a comfortable sofa and chair for reading or relaxing. From the porch, you can even catch a glimpse of Lowell Observatory, located just up the street. Nearby attractions include frisbee golf and Thorpe Park, complete with a children's playground and tennis courts. The property owner resides on-site, just below your space, and is more than happy to offer suggestions for dining and activities during your stay.One important note: The exterior staircase leading to the entrance has been recently rebuilt and is well-lit with solar lighting. However, please keep in mind that it may not be suitable for very young children or individuals with mobility issues. If this is a concern, we have ground-level accommodations available in the Aspen and Park Historic Homes that may better suit your needs – feel free to inquire!Situated in Flagstaff's downtown historic district, our home provides a convenient stopover for those venturing to the Grand Canyon. You'll find yourself within a couple of blocks of the downtown area, where bars, shops, restaurants, and the train station await. Thorpe Park, offering frisbee golf, tennis courts, and a children's play area, as well as Lowell Observatory, are just a short stroll up the street.Guest accessThe entire upstairs suite plus access to the shared back yardOther things to noteOur historic home has many great modern features but heating and cooling are not one of them. We do have a central heating system in the winter along with extra portable units. In the hotter summer months, we supply a window unit and a portable air conditioning system for this space plus fans to keep you comfortable. This is a second-floor unit so stairs are required. There is the potential to hear noise from your neighbors.

property_address: Entire home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Our luxuriously appointed loft apartment is the best of small space living. You'll find everything you need to relax and unwind (or work from "home"), with a fully equipped kitchen and laundry. The location puts you in easy walking distance to NAU and all that downtown has to offer. Off-street gated parking, easy self check-in, HEPA filtration, and enhanced cleaning procedures are all in place to make your stay safe and secure. Click "show more" for full details.The spaceSmall pleasures abound in this space; from the bedroom loft, take in a mountain view and the glow of Flagstaff's iconic Hotel Monte Vista sign at night-- sprawl out on the comfy couch, or curl up in the reading chair downstairs-- simply watch the clouds drift by through the artfully placed upper window, where you see nothing but sky from the lower level. Modernists will enjoy features like the soft glow of the vintage Nelson bubble lamp in the evenings, and clean lines of the Floyd furnishings chosen for this space. At the end of the day, sink into the comfort of the Tuft & Needle mattress and linen bedding from Parachute Home. You'll also find a well-equipped kitchen with quality cookware, chef's knives, and a gas stove with a griddle. There's plenty of dishware and glassware, and a dishwasher to make cleaning up easy. Options for your morning coffee ritual include pour-over, French press, or conventional coffeemaker. We also provide a small selection of tea and hot chocolate. Tech amenities include strong wi-fi, a smart TV with content from Amazon and Netflix, and an Echo voice-activated speaker. Organic soaps, lotion, and shampoo/conditioner are among the many little luxuries you'll find. Gated off-street parking for up to two cars is included.The Loft is a modern addition to a historic house. You'll have your own private entrance, but be aware that there is a shared wall with the main house-- we ask our guests in both spaces to be considerate of one another, but it's very likely you'll hear some muffled noise from the other side of the house. The heating system can make a bit of noise, too. The Loft is also located on a main street with frequent traffic. Guests who are seeking a quiet, isolated get-away will not find this to be the right property for them, but those who enjoy an urban vibe (even in our small town!) will feel at home.Your co-host, Anna, lives in the neighborhood and will be just a few blocks away should you need anything. She's a long-time Flagstaff resident and experienced Airbnb host with great recommendations and local insights-- just ask! Otherwise, we'll leave you to enjoy your stay, with convenient self check-in and check-out.Other things to noteAccess to The Loft is only through the rear of the property, which is served by a fire alley off of the main street. If you plan to receive deliveries (Instacart, USPS, UPS, etc.), please know that they will be delivered to the front house, which is our other Airbnb unit. The address of the main house serves both of our Airbnb units. You are welcome to coordinate your deliveries with the co-host, who can assist in providing you access through the south gate of the property (this gate is usually locked, but can be opened for you upon request).Should you have any trouble finding the place during check in, Anna the co host will be on call to assist you. To request help with deliveries, please message Anna as soon as you know you'll be receiving a package. Thank you!

listing_description: Hi, we are Jason & Nicole and we have 4 kids. We love being in the outdoors. One of our mottos is "if you ever run into a fork in the road always choose the one that offers the biggest adventure". As a family, we love to vacation and experience different parts of the world. We want others to see and appreciate this beautiful world we live in. Here is a space that might help you do just that.The spaceThis newly remodeled apartment at the base of Mount Elden has a private entrance to the right of the house, through the gate, and up the stairs. First thing you will see is the balcony where you can sit and enjoy the fresh air and views of Mount Elden under a giant 500 year old oak tree. Inside this 600 foot apartment you will enter into the main living area which is open to a full kitchen. In the kitchen is a full refrigerator, microwave, dishwasher and double oven (upper oven for broiling only). Basic kitchen items such as a Keurig coffee maker, knives, cutting boards, pots and pans, pyrex dishes, toaster, waffle maker, blender, and cookie sheet are provided for you to make your own meals. We have coffee, creamer and sugar available for you.After the long day of adventures or if your here to just relax, do it on our couch with a 55 inch Roku smart tv. It is logged into Netflix, Amazon Prime, and Disney Plus. Feel free to log into your own account to access your own watch list. We do not have cable. There are 2 bedrooms. One room has a king size bed and the other has a queen. Both rooms have a dresser and closet space with hangers.The bathroom has full size shower/tub combo. Shampoo, conditioner, and body wash are available. There is also a blow dryer.Flagstaff is a mountain town at 7000 ft elevation which cools down once the sun sets. We do have a portable AC unit in the main room that cools the place down nicely! You can also enjoy the cool mountain air with the fans and open windows in the evening and nights.We as a family live in the main part of the house. There is a door connecting the two that always remains locked. There is no sharing of any space! There will be some daily living sounds. We have kids and dogs that you might hear in the back yard. And any where you stay in Flagstaff you can hear the train.Our cul-de-sac has access to the national forest and Flagstaff trail systems which means you can hit the trails without getting in your car.There is room for one car on the RIGHT side of the driveway. ** Street parking is restricted from midnight to 7am November 1 to April 1 due to our city winter ordinance.** Any other time of the year, free street parking is available 24/7.

property_address: Entire rental unit in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Park on the premises and walk 3 blocks to the center of Historic Downtown Flagstaff. Second floor apartment so there are stairs, 2 separate bedrooms, well stocked kitchen. Skylights providing pleasant natural lighting throughout. Safe neighborhood, quiet evenings and weekends, a relaxing place and so close to downtown! There is no A/C and no TV but plenty of reading material about the area and games for spending quality time with your companions. I have 3 separate places all next to each other.The spaceThere is one outside flight of stairs to the second floor apartment. The apartment is completely separate and private from the downstairs apartment where the host lives. Provided for you is one off-street parking space for a small to medium sized vehicle. Two separate bedrooms each with a queen bed and a door for privacy. An open living room, kitchen and dining area. Bathroom has a shower and bathtub, plus fresh towels, many essentials (see Amenities List) and lots of shelves to spread out.There is ample storage in each bedroom or in a walk-in closet off the living room to store your luggage. Plenty of quality towels and wash rags, variety of hand and hair soaps, body lotion, hair dryer and miscellaneous toiletries should you have forgotten something.Six skylights throughout the place, 5 of which open providing wonderful lighting and fresh air.Comfortably accommodates up to 2 couples. If you have a need for more spaces for sleeping than the 2 queen beds can provide, please inquire with me first to see if I can accommodate your extra need.Kitchen is equipped with a convection countertop oven, a 2-burner hotplate, microwave oven, Mr. Coffee 12 cup coffee maker, electric kettle, full set of quality pots and pans including dishes for the microwave, plenty of dishes, glasses for adult beverages and all the things needed for preparation of most simple meals. A Brita filter also provided for filtered water. I have tried to think of all the basics that I would like to have myself in the kitchen but if there is anything you need, just ask me.Complimentary consumables provided include a variety of teas (black, green and herbal), coffee, sugar, cream, basic spices, olive oil and balsamic vinegar. There are many local shops selling a variety of beer and wine within minutes of walking I could direct you to, some are bars so will be open late. Or bring your favorite with you and enjoy in the comfort of this pleasant space!There is no TV and no air conditioning in the home. During the summer months, there are fans in every room and five skylights that open for cross air flow. Being a second floor apartment, it can get warm during the day in the summer months (June through August). However, once the Monsoon begins, generally mid-July, nights tend to cool down. If you are wanting to hang out in the apartment during the day or if you have young children who need mid day naps, it might be a consideration that on the very warmest days it maybe too warm. I do have an evaporative cooler for the living room.Guest accessI will meet you upon your arrival and take you into the apartment, give a short orientation of the space and give you keys. In the rare occasion that I will not be able to meet you, I will let you know and make sure you get keys.Other things to noteFlagstaff can cool down at nights so bring enough covering to be comfortable in the evening hours and do remember we are at 7,000 feet, which take time to adjust to this elevation for some. Be kind to yourself if you feel a bit out of breath, a nice walk downtown and the fresh mountain air will be a big help and real treat, enjoy!
