property_address: Entire home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Escape the ordinary and experience the magic of Flagstaff from the comfort of this exceptional mountain home. Whether you're seeking outdoor adventure, relaxation, or a bit of both, this spacious retreat offers the perfect base for your Flagstaff getaway. Nestled in the heart of Flagstaff, Arizona. 5 minutes to NAU and 10 minutes from Downtown. This quant cottage offers a harmonious blend of modern comfort and rustic charm.The spaceWelcome to our spacious and luxurious retreat!Overview:Our large home is the perfect choice for a family or small group to stay. With 2 bedrooms , 2 bathrooms, and a nice common areas, you'll have plenty of room to relax and unwind.Bedrooms:Our home features 2 beautifully appointed bedrooms, each designed with your comfort in mind. We have the bunk bed room that sleeps 5 and then the master bedroom that sleeps 2. Each bedroom is thoughtfully decorated and equipped with high-quality linens to ensure a restful night's sleep.Bathrooms:You'll find 2 pristine bathrooms throughout the house, complete with modern fixtures and plush towels. Getting ready for the day or winding down at night will be a breeze in these well-appointed spaces.Living Spaces:Our living areas are spacious and inviting, perfect for lounging and socializing. The open-concept design allows for seamless flow between the living room, dining area, and kitchen. You'll find our home is designed for relaxation and convenience.Kitchen:The chef in your group will love our fully equipped kitchen. It is stocked with everything you need to prepare delicious meals, from stainless steel appliances to ample counter space. Enjoy your meals at the dining table or take them outside to the various outdoor tables.Outdoor Space:Speaking of the outdoors, our home boasts a beautiful patio with a dining table and BBQ grill where you can soak up the sun or stargaze in the evening. And for the kids we've got a tree house and lots to play and climb on letting their imaginations run wild on our 2.5 forested acres.Other things to noteWe call this home the guest house as it's the smaller home of the two homes on the property. Both homes share a driveway but the drive splits so you have your own space to park in front of the home. Each of the homes have their own outside patio for your private use, but the forested 2.5 acres are available for both guests in the main house and the guest house to share.People love to visit Northern Arizona for its cooler temperatures in the summer and playing in the snow in the winter. We feel lucky to live here and like getting to share this with you, but snow in the winter can cause some logistical obstacles. As hosts, we will do our very best to keep pathways and driveways clear for guests, but it's not uncommon for Flagstaff to receive a foot or two of snow in a short period of time and this makes snow removal a challenge. Snow does create some obstacles for hosts and guests alike, so we want to be sure guests can know what to expect from us during the snowier times of year and what we in return ask of our guests.1) Guests can expect that prior to their arrival the driveway and paths to the home have been plowed at some point during the day of their arrival. However, if the driveway is plowed in the morning and more snow falls between morning time and check in you may arrive to the day's accumulation of snow on the drive. Guests can either drive over the snow or clear the snow with shovels provided. We only are able to do snow removal once a day. We do our very best to time our snow removal at the end of storms, but it doesn't always work out that way.2) THE BERMS! Any and every Flagstaff or Williams resident dreads the berm removal. What is the berm? The berm is a pile of snow at the end of your driveway caused by the snowplows pushing the snow from the streets to the side. There is nothing worse than shoveling your entire driveway only to have the plow come by and make a big berm you now have to clear before you can leave. We ALL dread the berm. As hosts we have NO WAY of knowing when the plows will come by. Because of this, it is possible that guests will arrive to a plowed driveway with a Berm at the end. If this happens guests will need to either drive over the berm (vehicle dependent) or use the provided shovels to make enough of an entry for your car to get through. Our snow removal crew will be around within the next 24 hours to take care of the rest. We are not a hotel with full time snow removal, so should you arrive during a snowstorm please know we are doing our best.3) Finally, something we love about Flagstaff is the sun after the snow, BUT this does mean the snow melts during the day and the wet turns into ice at night. We have a bucket with ice melt our guests are welcome to use on icy areas. Please only use it if there is ice as the salt is not good for the cement and trees. Also use sparingly as a little salt goes a long way.

property_address: Entire home in Flagstaff, Arizona, United States
listing_description: Panoramic mountain views from floor-to-ceiling windows are only the beginning of the exquisite features found in this luxury Flagstaff home. A blend of modern design and warm wood tones create a sophisticated space that will impress even the most seasoned traveler. Add in a nice list of amenities including all ensuite bedrooms, radiant heated floors, game loft, elevated hot tub & fire table deck, A/C, and 3 minutes to Snowbowl basecamp. Guests are ensured a stay beyond the everyday ordinary!The spaceEvery element in this 3,100 SF two-story home with incredible views and outdoor living space has been executed to perfection. Set against a panoramic backdrop of endless mountain views in the popular ski area of north Flagstaff, the showstopper at this stunning house is the amazing view that can be enjoyed from nearly every room. Floor to ceiling windows in the main social areas beautifully showcase vistas of the area’s rugged mountains, and every corner of the residence has been expertly styled with a refined modern flair to provide a getaway experience like no other. A gorgeous kitchen anchors one end of the main living area and features stainless-steel appliances, a gas range, waterfall island with bar seating, and a deluxe housewares & small appliances package. In the middle, the dining area makes a statement with a custom live-edge wood table for 10, designer lighting, and sightlines to the outdoors. On the far end of the room a plush seating area with fireplace and 24-foot ceiling is ideal for watching the Smart TV, but this takes a backseat to magnificent wraparound views of the mountains. This area also has walkout access to the lower patio where another table for 10 sits under event lighting for outdoor dining with a view.Three ensuite bedrooms with king beds, smart TVs, and plenty of storage for tucking way travel items are also found on the main floor. Bedroom 1 has an exquisite bathroom with freestanding tub/shower room & dual vanity sinks + walk-in closet. Bedroom 2 has a dedicated workspace and its ensuite bath is a work of art with custom blue and gold marble tile work in the walk-in shower. Bedroom 3 has a comfy reading nook, and the bathroom is sleek and roomy with a shower/tub combo and contemporary lighting. Need to wash clothes during your stay? There is a full laundry room with separate washer & dryer on the first floor as well. Head upstairs to find a neat bunkroom with ensuite bathroom, one twin XL bunk, and one queen bunk to sleep a total of six. A loft game room with a pool table, shuffleboard, TV viewing corner, and board games is up here, too, along with arguably the best spot in the house to take in the views: bar seating that overlooks picture windows perfectly framing the San Francisco Peaks in the distance. Access the upper deck through a sliding door to enjoy the hot tub, fire pit table, and more of those fantastic mountain views. And when it’s time for ground level fun, there is corn hole, a bbq, and plenty of room to stretch your legs on the oversized lot.When not spending time at this wonderful home, the base entry road to Snowbowl ski resort is only 1.2 miles away, and the property is on the opposite side of traffic which makes accessing the ski resort so easy! Endless hiking and mountain biking trails are within close proximity, downtown Flagstaff is just 8 miles from the home, Sedona is only 37 miles, and in 67 minutes you can be at the Grand Canyon.Welcome to your vacation!Guest accessThe entire house and surrounding grounds including the lower porch and upper deck, front yard, back yard, and driveway in front of the house are exclusively available to guests. The detached garage and driveway in front of garage are not available for guest use, however there is parking in front of house including space for trucks/SUVs. We ask that you do not bring more than 5 vehicles unless otherwise approved by host prior to arrival. Hosts may be on site in separate living quarters.Other things to noteThe minimum age to rent this home is 25. Pets are not allowed at this home, thank you for understanding.Coconino County Permit: STR-23-0144TPT Number: 21515635

Here are some of the many options available to you:✔ Walnut Canyon National Monument: Located just southeast of Flagstaff, Walnut Canyon National Monument offers breathtaking views and the opportunity to explore ancient cliff dwellings. Visitors can hike along the trails and learn about the history and culture of the Sinagua people who once inhabited the area.✔ Sunset Crater Volcano National Monument: This unique geological site features a volcanic cone and lava flow from an eruption that occurred nearly 900 years ago. The observatory is famous for its discovery of Pluto and continues to contribute to astronomical research.✔ Arizona Snowbowl: If you're visiting during the winter months or enjoy outdoor activities in the snow, Arizona Snowbowl is a popular destination for skiing and snowboarding. property_address: Entire cabin in Williams, Arizona, United States
listing_description: The Wright Hill Cabin is located in the small, rural community of Parks, Arizona - 20 minutes West of Flagstaff and 15 minutes East of Williams. Situated just within the tree line, the cabin sits on the edge of beautiful Government Prairie which provides unobstructed views of the San Francisco Peaks while providing the beautiful scenery and wildlife of the vast Ponderosa Pine Forest. The quiet community of Parks provides easy access to Grand Canyon National Park, Snowbowl, Bearizona and more!The spaceThe Wright Hill Cabin is a small (~900Sq. ft.), but cozy 2 bedroom/1 bathroom home that provides incredible views in a comfortable and quiet setting. The cabin is situated on 5.5 acres that borders Forest Service Land (Public) and has direct, private access to the Kaibab National Forest. One bedroom is outfitted with a King sized mattress and TV and the other with a Queen sized mattress. Both bedrooms have closet space. The common area offers TV, large leather couch, dinette, wood burning stove, and French Doors that lead to a wrap-around, covered porch. A small laundry/mud room outfitted with a small washer/dryer combo leads to a fully equipped kitchen. Comfortable patio furniture, propane BBQ, and incredible views make it difficult to head inside for bed at the end of the evening.Guest accessThe whole house and property is yours to enjoy! A large detached garage, located behind the house, will NOT be accessible to guests. Immediate access from the property directly to the Kaibab National Forest and an endless amount of off-road vehicle and hiking trails.Other things to noteWATER:Water is a valuable resource in the arid Southwest... and water on this property is hauled. With that being said, use water in a respectful manner. - Please fill dishwater entirely before running or hand washing any dishes- Do not let shower run excessively prior to entering - hot water delivered fast- Do not let faucets run excessively - turn off when washing/brushingACCESS: Maintained dirt road accessible with 2 wheel drive and low clearance. MAP provided with detailed directionsTV:Entertainment Apps accessible Netflix provided WIFI:STARLINK - High Speed InternetCELL SERVICE:VERIZON cell service at the cabin is reliable. Other cell providers will likely be spotty at the cabin, but finding service in the general area should not be an issue. AIR-FRYER & KEURIG**WINTER SEASON RESERVATIONS**- I must make you aware that I have to manage my cabin very carefully In the winter time due to the potential for major winter weather events. Your reservation can only be Gauranteed as far as the weather forecast can predict.. furthermore, I reserve the right to cancel any reservation that may be Impacted by winter weather. This is ultimately for the Safety of my guests and myself. IF A RESERVATION MUST BE CANCELED DUE TO WINTER WEATHER, I WILL PERSONALLY REACH OUT TO AIRBNB TO ENSURE A FULL REFUND AND NO PENALIZATION FOR CANCELATION. Access to the property Is overall reliable, However I-40 can be very Dangerous and It often closes during big snow storms. This interstate in the only route to and from Parks. The road leading to the cabin Is dirt and must be plowed continuously during storms and even with that effort, It is often trecherous even with 4WD. I understand that many guests travel to the area for winter storms, and I will do my best to accommodate your stay, but safety is the ultimate concern. PLEASE be aware that I will keep a very very close watch on the weather as your reservation approaches and communicate very thoroughly so that we can plan your trip Safely or cancel In a timely manner.Permit #: STR-24-0468
